<?php require_once __DIR__.'/../includes/app-layout.php'; $wallet=bos_page_start('Beyond OS','Privacy Policy','Beyond OS Privacy Policy.'); ?><main class="bos-main"><section class="bos-hero"><span class="bos-kicker">Privacy</span><h1>Your data across Beyond OS</h1><p>Beyond ID connects app activity, preferences, wallet history and subscriptions. Sensitive journal and wellness information should be private by default and access-controlled.</p></section><section class="bos-section"><h2>First-party visitor analytics</h2><p>Beyond OS records privacy-conscious traffic metrics such as page views, app sections, device category, browser family and referring domain. Visitor identifiers are one-way hashed with a protected key stored outside the public web root. Raw IP addresses, full user-agent strings and URL query parameters are not stored, and browser Do Not Track signals are respected.</p></section><section class="bos-section"><h2>Data controls</h2><p>Users can review profile information, active sessions and app connections. Production deployment should include retention schedules, export and deletion workflows, encryption, access logging and consent records.</p></section></main><?php bos_page_end(); ?>